# MLIS Fees Solution Design (Revised)
 
## 1. Objective
Deliver MLIS fee support across Submission (Opportunity), Quote, and Policy with this exact start model:
- Submission can start from two paths:
  - MLIS Portal (Experience Cloud)
  - Salesforce QuoteJourney tab
- Both paths create New Business Submission/Quote and can be finalized to Policy.
- At Submission creation, create MLIS Fee__c automatically with a default NB value (example: GBP 10).
- Underwriter can adjust fee value from Opportunity (while Submission is not Live) using a button and modal.
- MTA follows the same pattern as NB but with its own default MTA fee value.
- Cancellation and Cancel and Reissue follow the same existing process used in Oliva/Asset.
 
## 2. UX Design
### 2.1 Opportunity Control
- Add Opportunity quick action/button: Manage MLIS Fee.
- Position and behavior should follow existing Edit Premium / Limit of Indemnity pattern.
- Visibility: Underwriter only.
- Portal users cannot edit fee values.
 
### 2.2 Modal Design (Opportunity)
Fields:
- Apply MLIS Fee (toggle)
- Transaction context (NB or MTA)
- Default fee (read-only)
- Override fee amount (currency input)
- Range slider for override amount (same min/max rules as configured governance)
- Override reason (mandatory when override differs from default)
 
Behavior:
- Load default fee by context (NB/MTA) from configuration.
- Keep amount input and slider synchronized.
- Validate on save: range, permissions, lock state.
 
### 2.3 Locking Rules
- If Submission/Opportunity is Live: no fee edits allowed.
- If policy is Forced: no fee edits allowed.
- Show clear reason message when blocked.
 
## 3. Data and Processing Design
### 3.1 Default Values
- NB default fee configured value (example: GBP 10).
- MTA default fee configured separately (can be different from NB).
 
### 3.2 Fee__c Creation Rules
- On NB Submission creation (from either Portal or QuoteJourney), create Fee__c immediately using NB default.
- On MTA creation, create/update Fee__c using MTA default.
- If valid Opportunity override exists and record is editable, use override value.
- Prevent duplicate active Fee__c records per transaction instance.
 
### 3.3 Cancellation and Cancel & Reissue
- Follow existing established process used by Oliva/Asset.
- Do not introduce a separate MLIS-specific cancellation engine in this phase.
 
## 4. Integration Scope
- Quote Results: show MLIS Fee line and updated totals.
- Quote Summary: show MLIS Fee line and updated totals.
- Documents where premium/total is shown:
  - Quote Document
  - Specimen Policy Document
  - Final Draft
  - Policy Document
  - Debit Note
- Optional BDX mapping remains toggle-based.
 
## 5. Security and Audit
- Underwriter-only fee edit permission on Opportunity.
- Portal path can initiate Submission/Quote but cannot edit fee via modal.
- Audit log for overrides:
  - who changed
  - when changed
  - old value
  - new value
  - reason
 
## 6. Acceptance Highlights
- NB fee is created automatically at Submission creation from both start paths.
- Default NB fee is applied (example: GBP 10) unless valid override exists.
- Underwriter can change fee only when Submission is not Live.
- MTA uses its own default fee and same modal/override rules.
- Cancellation and Cancel & Reissue follow existing Oliva/Asset process.
- Fee displays correctly in quote views and in-scope documents.
 
## 7. Delivery Components
- Opportunity UI:
  - Manage MLIS Fee button
  - modal with fields + slider + validation
- Service logic:
  - resolve default fee by context (NB/MTA)
  - apply override precedence and lock checks
  - create Fee__c on NB Submission creation
  - create/update Fee__c on MTA creation
  - duplicate prevention
- Rendering:
  - quote/result/summary
  - document generation outputs
  - optional BDX
- Testing:
  - Portal-start NB
  - QuoteJourney-start NB
  - MTA default and override
  - lock conditions
  - cancellation/cancel-reissue regression alignment with existing process
 
